- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also likely as the paper deals with infinite words and their factorizations, which are central topics in formal languages and automata theory.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is another possible category as the paper may involve some information-theoretic concepts related to the compression of palindromic factorizations.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper may involve some complexity analysis of the palindromic factorizations.
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper may involve some geometric interpretations or applications of the palindromic factorizations.
